      "reading_order": 5,
      "text": "When plant or animals die, part of\ntheir body is eaten by scavengers\nlike vultures, crows and so on.\nThe uneaten parts are acted upon\nby microorganisms such as fungi\nand bacteria known as\ndecomposers. The decomposers break\ndown or decompose the dead\nmaterial into nutrients and\nhelp to return the nutrients\nto the soil. These nutrients\nare absorbed by plants again\nto make food."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "20260214_5844806d-4167-4224-ac2f-075855bfcc78_10_block_003",
